<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880817-0014 </DOCNO><HL> Winston Furniture Seeks Alternate Buyer </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WF </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> BIRMINGHAM, Ala.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Winston Furniture Co. said it is seeking another buyer as an alternative to a $27.9 million merger with a private investment company controlled by three of Winston's directors.    The aluminum and wrought-iron furniture maker, based here, said it has hired Wheat First Securities Inc. as its exclusive agent for finding a more attractive merger. In July, Winston signed a letter of intent with Atlanta-based River Capital Inc. providing for the merger but allowing Winston to terminate the transaction in favor of a more attractive offer. </TEXT></DOC>